headline: Is It Time To Reassess Copart (CPRT) After A 31% One Year Share Price Decline
summary: If you are wondering whether Copart's share price still makes sense after a long run on the market, you are not alone. This article focuses squarely on what you might be paying for the underlying business. Over the short term, Copart's stock has been mixed, with a 1.7% decline over the last 7 days, a 5.1% gain over the last 30 days, and a 5.1% return year to date. headline: 2 Large-Cap Stocks for Long-Term Investors and 1 We Avoid
summary: Large-cap stocks usually command their industries because they have the scale to drive market trends. The flip side though is that their sheer size can limit growth as expanding further becomes an increasingly challenging task.
